## Growth
It's been cool to watch the rationalist community change so much over the past few years. 

It almost feels like the community I'm writing about is a thing of the past already--as of 2017 or 2018. Something I didn't understand when I was first out of college was that people can and do change, but also often as their entire community changes. 
I'm not sure what's harder, for an individual, or for a community to all change together. I hadn't seen, at the time, an example of a community changing its beliefs because of collective action, and honestly, working towards change felt futile. 
There are people within the movement who provide alternative views and often criticism. 
